261
00:12:14,794 --> 00:12:16,565
They're gonna tell us at the assembly.

262
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:18,634
Who's Jason and what happened to him?

263
00:12:19,465 --> 00:12:21,771
Thank you for that moment of silence.

264
00:12:21,773 --> 00:12:23,372
Many of you were lucky enough

265
00:12:23,374 --> 00:12:25,474
to have known my brother personally.

266
00:12:25,499 --> 00:12:29,431
Each and every one of you
meant the world to Jason.

267
00:12:29,456 --> 00:12:31,614
I loved my brother.

268
00:12:31,616 --> 00:12:34,650
He was and always will be my soulmate.

269
00:12:35,386 --> 00:12:36,685
So I speak with the confidence

270
00:12:36,687 --> 00:12:38,480
only a twin could have...

271
00:12:38,505 --> 00:12:42,091
Jason wouldn't want us to
spend the year mourning.

272
00:12:42,798 --> 00:12:46,724
Jason would want us to
move on with our lives.

273
00:12:46,749 --> 00:12:48,431
Which is why I've asked the School Board

274
00:12:48,433 --> 00:12:50,566
not to cancel the
Back-to-School semiformal.

275
00:12:52,103 --> 00:12:53,305
But rather, to let us use it

276
00:12:53,330 --> 00:12:56,172
as a way to heal, collectively,

277
00:12:56,174 --> 00:13:00,109
and celebrate my brother's too,
too short life on this mortal coil.

278
00:13:01,045 --> 00:13:02,511
Thank you all.

279
00:13:08,680 --> 00:13:11,128
- Ms. Grundy? Hey.
- Archie.

280
00:13:11,715 --> 00:13:14,133
What are you doing walking in this heat?

281
00:13:14,158 --> 00:13:15,658
Um... Building character?

282
00:13:18,196 --> 00:13:19,395
Do you want a ride?

283
00:13:36,973 --> 00:13:42,077
